description: The underlying index is an equally weighted index of large-capitalization securities. The fund generally will invest in all of the securities that comprise its underlying index in proportion to their weightings in the underlying index. It invests, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the value of its assets (net assets plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in securities of large-capitalization U.S. issuers.
name: IQ Chaikin U.S. Large Cap ETF
